截至北京时间3月22日12时，除中国外，184个国家和地区累计确诊222707例新冠肺炎，“钻石公主”号邮轮712例。
As of 12: 00 noon March 22, Beijing time, in addition to China, 184 countries and regions have confirmed a cumulative total of 222,707 cases of new crown pneumonia, "Princess Diamond" 712 cases.
当前，欧美疫情仍旧快速蔓延。
The epidemic is still spreading rapidly in Europe and the United States.
其中，意大利病例突破5万例，总理孔特要求全国停止所有非必要的生产活动。
With more than 50,000 cases reported in Italy, Prime Minister Conte has called for a nationwide halt to all non-essential production.
美国、西班牙、德国、伊朗四国21日确诊数字突破2万例。
The United States, Spain, Germany, Iran 21 confirmed the number of more than 20,000 cases.
此外，新加坡宣布禁止所有外国人入境或过境。
In addition, Singapore has declared a ban on the entry or transit of all foreigners.
意大利全国停止非必要生产活动根据当地时间3月22日18时意大利卫生部公布的最近数据，意大利现有新冠病毒患者46638例，死亡5476例，治愈7024例，累计确诊感染新冠病毒总人数为59138例，较3月21日18时新增5560例，意大利新增死亡651例。
According to the latest data released by the Italian Ministry of Health at 1800 hours local time on March 22, Italy now has 4,6638 new cases of Crested Virus, 5,476 deaths and 7,024 cures, bringing the total number of confirmed new cases to 59138, an increase of 5,560 since 18.00 on March 21 and 651 new deaths in Italy.
当地时间21日晚，意大利总理孔特通过社交媒体直播宣布，为了尽快遏制疫情蔓延，全国停止所有非必要的生产活动，在非必要情况下应实行远程办公。
In order to halt the spread of the epidemic as soon as possible, all non-essential production activities will be halted and telecommuting will be introduced if necessary, Prime Minister Konte announced on the evening of the 21st local time.
此外，他还强调超市仍将继续营业，民众不要排长队抢购食品。
He also stressed that supermarkets would remain open and people would not have to wait in long lines to buy food.
孔特说，当前的疫情是意大利自二战后遇到的“最严峻的危机”。
Conte said the current outbreak was "the most severe crisis" Italy has faced since World War II.
防控措施需要时间显现效果，意大利人要坚持住，不要失去对未来的希望，团结就可以战胜疫情。
Prevention and control measures take time to show results, and Italians can overcome the epidemic by staying the course and not losing hope for the future.
意大利卫生专家表示，目前为止，意大利死亡病例平均年龄已从80.5岁降至80岁，确诊患者的平均年龄也降为了63岁。
Italian health experts say the average age of deaths in Italy has fallen from 80.5 to 80 years so far, and the average age of confirmed patients has fallen to 63.
意大利新冠病毒应急委员会专员博雷利称，意大利的疫情峰值可能需要一周甚至更久才能到来。
Italy's peak could take a week or more, said Italy's top official with the New Crown Virus Emergency Response Board.
据央视新闻，当地时间21日，意大利AC米兰足球俱乐部在官网发布公告称，球队技术总监保罗·马尔蒂尼于前一天接受新冠病毒核酸试剂检测的结果呈阳性。
Italy's AC Milan Football Club announced on its official website Thursday that its technical director, Paolo Maldini, had tested positive for the new strain of nucleic acid the day before, CCTV reported.
同时他的儿子，AC米兰队中场球员丹尼尔·马尔蒂尼也感染了新冠病毒。
Meanwhile, his son, AC Milan midfielder Daniel Maldini, has also been infected with the new Crown virus.
公告称，马尔蒂尼和儿子目前身体状况良好，在知道自己和新冠肺炎确诊患者有密切接触之后，已在家隔离了两周时间。
Maldini and her son are now in good health and have been kept in isolation for two weeks after learning of their close contact with patients diagnosed with pneumonia.
他们将继续隔离直至康复。
They will remain isolated until they recover.
同一天，意甲尤文图斯俱乐部前锋迪巴拉在自己的社交媒体账号上公布了自己和女友感染新型冠状病毒的消息。
On the same day, Italian club striker DiBarra announced on his social media account that he and his girlfriend were infected with the new coronavirus.
他是继鲁加尼和马图伊迪之后，尤文第三名确诊感染的球员。
He was the third player to be diagnosed with infection after Rugani and Matuidi.
新加坡"封国"央视新闻3月22日消息，新加坡跨部门工作小组负责人黄循财今天（22日）宣布，由于新冠肺炎确诊病例快速增长，其中绝大部分是输入病例。
Singapore & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot
因此为了遏制疫情蔓延，从23日23时59分开始，禁止所有外国人入境或过境新加坡。
Therefore, in order to contain the spread of the epidemic, all foreigners are prohibited from entering or transiting through Singapore from 2359 hours on the 23rd.
此外，持有长期居留许可证件者中，只有从事医护、运输业的人士允许入境。
In addition, only persons engaged in medical care and transport are allowed to enter the country.
黄循财表示，新加坡马来西亚特别工作委员会已经达成一致，疫情期间持有工作准证的马来西亚人可以在住宿有保证的前提下返回新加坡继续工作。
Mr Wong said the Singapore-Malaysia Task Force had agreed that Malaysians holding work permits during the outbreak could return to Singapore with guaranteed accommodation to continue working.
新加坡跨部门合作，协助企业解决住宿。
Singapore works collaboratively across sectors to help businesses find accommodation.
新马之间货物运输不受限制。
There is no restriction on freight between horses.
澳大利亚“封国”澳大利亚总理莫里森19日宣布，从当地时间20日晚21点起，对所有非澳大利亚公民和非永久居民执行旅行禁令。
Australia's "Seal the Nation" Australian Prime Minister David Morrison announced Thursday that a travel ban would be imposed on all non-Australian citizens and non-permanent residents from 21: 00 pm local time.
据路透社报道，20日当天，数千人依旧涌到邦迪海滩。
Thousands of people still poured into Bondi Beach on Tuesday, Reuters reported.
大量人群在海滩聚集的照片引发了澳联邦卫生部长格雷格·亨特的强烈不满。
Photographs of crowds gathering on the beach have sparked outrage from the Australian Federal Health Secretary, Greg Hunt.
他表示，如此多人聚集在邦迪海滩是“令人无法接受的”。
He said it was "unacceptable" for so many people to gather at Bondi Beach.
当地时间21日下午，新南威尔士州警长大卫·埃利奥特宣布关闭邦迪海滩，因该沙滩人数已超过规定限制的户外聚集人数。
New South Wales police chief David Elliot announced the closure of Bondi Beach on the afternoon of Sunday, as the beach was already crowded with more people than the required number of people gathered outdoors.
此前，澳政府出台规定，禁止500人以上非必要性户外聚会。
Earlier, the Australian government introduced rules prohibiting outdoor gatherings of more than 500 people that were not necessary.
外媒：东京奥运开始草拟多种推迟方案北京时间3月22日，据路透社报道，两位知情人士透露，东京奥组委已经开始草拟今年夏季举办奥运会的可能替代方案。
TOKYO (Reuters) - The Tokyo Organizing Committee for the Olympic Games has begun drafting a possible alternative to hosting the games this summer, two people familiar with the matter said.
文章认为，这一举措与此前日本政府“不推迟奥运”形成鲜明对比。
The article said the move was in sharp contrast to previous efforts by the Japanese government to "not delay the Olympics."
据一位与东京奥组委关系密切的消息人士证实，东京奥组委内部确实正在讨论推迟的可能性，包括推迟一至两年。
A source close to the Tokyo Organizing Committee confirmed that the possibility of a delay, including a one-to-two-year delay, was indeed under discussion within the Tokyo Organizing Committee.
一位参与草拟方案的官员表示，一些奥组委内部的工作人员希望东京奥运会能够推迟一个月或45天。
One official involved in drafting the plan said some IOC staff wanted the Games to be delayed by a month or 45 days.
当然，是否会推迟的最终决定必须由国际奥委会做出，但日本方面的立场也很重要。
Of course, the final decision on whether or not to delay must be taken by the IOC, but the Japanese side's position is also important.
在路透社看来，即便奥运会改期也面临着诸多的不确定性。
According to Reuters, even the Olympics rescheduling faces a lot of uncertainty.
这家英国通讯社认为，2021年夏季赛历拥挤，其中欧洲杯已经移到了2021年，同时还有日本福冈游泳世锦赛。
The British news agency reckons the summer calendar for 2021 is crowded, with Euro 2021 and the Fukuoka Swimming World Championships.
到了2022年则更加拥挤，将有卡塔尔世界杯、杭州亚运会、北京冬奥会等。
By 2022 it will be even more crowded, with the World Cup in Qatar, the Asian Games in Hangzhou and the Winter Olympics in Beijing.
近50国宣布进入紧急状态 其中部分国家称“战时状态”！新冠肺炎疫情正在全球蔓延，截至北京时间3月22日中午12时许，据环球网统计发现，不到3天时间内，全球又有多国宣布进入紧急状态。
Nearly 50 countries have declared a state of emergency, some of which are called "wartime status.The outbreak of pneumonia is spreading all over the world, and a new global emergency was declared in less than three days, according to the World Wide Web at about 12: 00 noon Beijing time on March 22.
截至目前，全球至少已有48个国家宣布进入紧急状态。
At least 48 countries have declared a state of emergency so far.
已宣布进入紧急状态的国家包括：格鲁吉亚、多米尼加、葡萄牙、澳大利亚、萨尔瓦多、洪都拉斯、卢森堡、津巴布韦、哥伦比亚、约旦、纳米比亚、斯威士兰、苏丹、亚美尼亚、厄瓜多尔、芬兰、法国、摩尔多瓦、瑞士、哥斯达黎加、波黑、奥地利、塞浦路斯、黎巴嫩、塞尔维亚、南非、秘鲁、哈萨克斯坦、罗马尼亚、利比亚、西班牙、保加利亚、爱沙尼亚、波兰、巴拿马、美国、委内瑞拉、斯洛伐克、拉脱维亚、阿根廷、捷克、匈牙利、菲律宾、巴勒斯坦、危地马拉、韩国、立陶宛、意大利。
Countries that have declared a state of emergency include Georgia, Dominica, Portugal, Australia, El Salvador, Honduras, Luxembourg, Zimbabwe, Colombia, Jordan, Namibia, Swaziland, Sudan, Armenia, Ecuador, Finland, France, Moldova, Switzerland, Costa Rica, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Austria, Cyprus, Lebanon, Serbia, South Africa, Peru, Kazakhstan, Romania, Libya, Spain, Bulgaria, Estonia, Poland, Panama, Argentina,
其中，法国、韩国分别为“战时状态”、“战争状态”，葡萄牙历史上首次进入全国紧急状态。
Among them, France, South Korea for the "state of war," "state of war," Portugal for the first time in national emergency.
其他国家疫情最新消息西班牙或将国家紧急状态延长15天据西班牙卫生部22日公布的数据，西班牙较前日新增新冠肺炎确诊病例3646例，累计确诊病例达28572例，其中1720人死亡，2575人治愈出院。
Spain confirmed 3,646 new cases of pneumonia on Sunday, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 28,572, including 1,720 deaths and 2,575 cured, the Health Ministry said Wednesday.
据当地媒体报道，西班牙政府22日表示，为了遏制疫情，决定将该国原定15天的国家紧急状态延长15天，该决定需议会进一步批准生效。
Spain's decision to extend the country's original 15-day state of emergency for 15 days to contain the outbreak requires further parliamentary approval, local media reported Tuesday.
21日晚，根据西班牙媒体消息，皇马前主席洛伦索·桑斯因患新冠肺炎去世，享年76岁。
Real Madrid president Lorenzo Sands died of pneumonia at the age of 76, according to Spanish media reports Wednesday.
美国新增6670例新冠肺炎，确诊人数突破3万据美国约翰·霍普金斯大学发布的新冠肺炎数据实时统计系统显示，截至美国东部时间3月22日下午6点，美国共报告新冠肺炎确诊病例32717例，死亡409，治愈178例。
Up to 6: 00 pm on March 22, the United States had reported 32,717 confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia, 409 and 178 cases cured, according to the New Crown Pneumonia Statistics System released by Johns Hopkins University.
22日不到18小时时间里，美国新增确诊6670例。
Less than 18 hours on the 22nd, the United States confirmed 6,670 new cases.
目前，美国确诊病例数位居全球第三，仅次于中国和意大利。
The United States now has the third highest number of confirmed cases in the world, after China and Italy.
纽约州的确诊病例数占全美总数近一半，22日达到了15777例，一日内新增3463例。
Nearly half of all cases were diagnosed in New York state, reaching 15,777 on the 22nd, with 3,463 new cases in a day.
其中纽约市就占到了9654例，新增1539例。
New York City alone accounted for 9,654 cases, with 1,539 new cases.
其他确诊病例上千的州包括华盛顿州1996例，新泽西州1914例，加利福尼亚州1701例，伊利诺伊州1049例，密歇根州1035例。
Other states with thousands of confirmed cases include Washington State in 1996, New Jersey in 1914, California in 1701, Illinois in 1,049, and Michigan in 1,035.
法国新增1559例新冠肺炎，累计确诊升至16018例法国卫生总署署长热罗姆·萨洛蒙在22日的新闻发布会上通报说，截至当日法国累计确诊新冠肺炎病例16018例，较昨日新增1559例。
France added 1559 new cases of pneumonia, cumulative confirmed to 16,018 cases of French Director of Health Jérôme Salomon reported in a press conference on the 22, as of the same day France confirmed a total of 16,018 new cases of pneumonia, 1559 more than yesterday.
其中新增死亡112例，累计死亡674例，住院7240例，重症1746例。
There were 112 new deaths, 674 cumulative deaths, 7,240 hospitalizations and 1,746 severe cases.
伊朗新增1028例新冠肺炎 累计升至21638例伊朗卫生部3月22日宣布，过去24小时，伊朗新增新冠肺炎确诊病例1028例，新增死亡129例。
Iran adds 1028 new cases of pneumonia to 21,638 Iran's Ministry of Health announced Monday that it has opened 1,028 new cases of new cases of pneumonia and 129 new deaths in the past 24 hours.
目前该国累计确诊21638例，其中1685人死亡，7913人治愈。
At present, a total of 21,638 cases have been diagnosed in the country, of which 1,685 have died and 7,913 have been cured.
接触医生检测呈阳性 默克尔居家隔离据央视新闻，德国内阁计划将于3月23日启动一项金额达1500亿欧元的补充预算，用于满足下周末启动的针对疫情的快速援助计划，德国在各地已经部署了大约220名联邦技术救援署工作人员。
Germany's cabinet plans to launch a 150 billion euro supplemental budget on March 23 to meet a rapid response plan for the outbreak that starts next weekend, with about 220 federal technical assistance workers deployed around the country, CCTV said.
德国联邦食品及农业部部长尤利亚·戈洛克内尔指出德国有充足的食品供应，呼吁消费者不要抢购。
Germany's Federal Food and Agriculture Minister, Julia Gronell, said Germany had a plentiful supply of food and called on consumers not to snap it up.
22日，德国联邦政府发表声明，在获悉与自己接触的医生新冠肺炎病毒检测呈阳性后，德国总理默克尔已居家隔离。
German Chancellor Angela Merkel has been placed in quarantine after being tested positive for the new crown pneumonia virus, the German federal government said in a statement.
据悉，默克尔在本周日宣布新的疫情管控措施后不久被告知这一消息，该医生周五曾给默克尔注射肺炎链球菌疫苗。
Merkel was told the news shortly after announcing new measures on Sunday that she had been vaccinated with Streptococcus pneumoniae on Friday.
联邦政府发言人塞伯特称，默克尔将在未来几天接受“常规检查”，并暂时居家工作。
A federal spokesman, Robert Sebert, said Ms. Merkel would undergo 'routine checks' in the coming days and work temporarily from home.
